### Simulate multiple rapid requests (stress test)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/progress
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/time-remaining
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/progress
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### PERFORMANCE TEST 8: Memory Usage Test (Large Payloads)

### Submit answer with large explanation
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 6,
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 45,
  "ghiChu": "This is a very long note to test memory usage and performance with large text payloads. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum."
}

### PERFORMANCE TEST 9: Database Transaction Performance

### Rapid answer updates (test transaction handling)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 7,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 10
}

### Update same answer (test update performance)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 7,
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 15
}

### Update again (test repeated updates)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 7,
  "dapAnChon": "C",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 20
}

### PERFORMANCE TEST 10: Submission Performance

### Submit exam (test grading performance)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Immediately get results (test calculation speed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfSessionId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### PERFORMANCE MONITORING ENDPOINTS

### Check system performance metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/performance-metrics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Check database performance
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/database-stats
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Check memory usage
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/memory-usage
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### PERFORMANCE TEST 11: Cleanup Performance

### Test deletion performance
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfExamId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Verify cleanup completed quickly
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{perfExamId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### LOAD TEST SIMULATION (Run these in sequence quickly)

### Rapid fire requests to simulate high load
GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi?page=2&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi?page=3&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi?page=4&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi?page=5&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### EXPECTED PERFORMANCE BENCHMARKS:
# - Question creation: < 200ms
# - Exam creation with 50 questions: < 500ms
# - Session start: < 100ms
# - Answer submission: < 50ms
# - Anti-cheat logging: < 30ms
# - Question retrieval (paginated): < 150ms
# - Exam statistics calculation: < 300ms
# - Exam submission and grading: < 1000ms
# - Large data queries: < 500ms
# - Concurrent requests should not degrade performance significantly
# - Memory usage should remain stable under load
# - Database connections should be properly managed
# - No memory leaks during extended testing

### PERFORMANCE MONITORING NOTES:
# - Monitor response times for each request
# - Check for any timeouts or 500 errors
# - Verify memory usage doesn't grow excessively
# - Ensure database connections are released properly
# - Watch for any performance degradation over time
# - Test with realistic data volumes
# - Simulate real-world usage patterns